In a bowl, combine chili powder, ginger, garlic salt and pepper. Add beef strips and toss to coat. Set aside. Meanwhile, in a medium saucepan combine salsa, peanut butter, soy sauce, vinegar, molasses, Splenda and water. Bring to boiling, stirring often. Remove from heat. Set aside. In a large skillet or wok, heat oil over medium-high heat. Add beef and stir fry for 2-3 minutes, until cooked through. Add the sauce and stir thoroughly. Serve garnished with scallions.